&lt;p&gt;Ward-based Spinal Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time (flexible working options considered). Day shifts only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fancy trying something different, learning new skills and developing your therapy career? Well we have exactly what you are looking for. We have developed an exciting new OT role that involves working closely with the ward team and experienced rehabilitation assistants, enabling rehabilitation to be taken to a new level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the support of experienced Spinal Therapists and opportunities to develop specialist skills, working alongside ward colleagues and promoting rehabilitation in a truly interdisciplinary way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 39 bedded Regional Spinal Centre specialising in Spinal Cord Injury rehabilitation. We provide exceptional care for patients who have sustained either traumatic or non-traumatic life changing spinal cord injuries. Through a strong patient centered, multi professional approach we aim to promote independence, self-reliance and self-esteem, empowering our patients to live their life to the fullest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What our patients say about us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;“Exceptional Team from the bottom up” - Friends and family feedback&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“Outstanding in all areas” – &lt;em&gt;National Adult Inpatients Survey &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“A model Ward” - &lt;em&gt;National Adult Inpatients Survey &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“Outstanding Compassionate Care” – &lt;em&gt;Friends and Family Feedback&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our vision is to be outstanding every time, putting patients at the heart of everything that we do.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you take up the challenge of joining the Spinal Team we will ensure you thrive within our culture of self-improvement, staff development and positive exceptional practice. Whether you are a newly qualified therapist looking for a supportive first role, or looking for a new challenge we welcome you to join our positive, progressive and dynamic Spinal Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catherine Whitmarsh Therapy Team Leader catherine.whitmarsh@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spinal Matron Dawn Edge dawn.edge1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
